97 bool PropertyLinkBase::isSame(const Property& other) const
98 {
99  if (&other == this) {
100  return true;
101  }
102  if (other.isDerivedFrom(PropertyLinkBase::getClassTypeId())
103  || getScope() != static_cast<const PropertyLinkBase*>(&other)->getScope()) {
104  return false;
105  }
106 
107  static std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> ret;
108  static std::vector<std::string> subs;
109  static std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> ret2;
110  static std::vector<std::string> subs2;
111 
112  ret.clear();
113  subs.clear();
114  ret2.clear();
115  subs2.clear();
116  getLinks(ret, true, &subs, false);
117  static_cast<const PropertyLinkBase*>(&other)->getLinks(ret2, true, &subs2, true);
118 
119  return ret == ret2 && subs == subs2;
120 }

122 void PropertyLinkBase::unregisterElementReference()
123 {
124  for (auto obj : _ElementRefs) {
125  auto it = _ElementRefMap.find(obj);
126  if (it != _ElementRefMap.end()) {
127  it->second.erase(this);
128  if (it->second.empty()) {
129  _ElementRefMap.erase(it);

131  }
132  }
133  _ElementRefs.clear();

150 void PropertyLinkBase::getLabelReferences(std::vector<std::string>& subs, const char* subname)
151 {
152  const char* dot;
153  for (; (subname = strchr(subname, '$')) != nullptr; subname = dot + 1) {
154  ++subname;
155  dot = strchr(subname, '.');
156  if (!dot) {
157  break;
158  }
159  subs.emplace_back(subname, dot - subname);
160  }
161 }

189 std::string PropertyLinkBase::updateLabelReference(const App::DocumentObject* parent,
190  const char* subname,
191  App::DocumentObject* obj,
192  const std::string& ref,
193  const char* newLabel)
194 {
195  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument() || !parent || !parent->isAttachedToDocument()) {
196  return {};
197  }
198 
199  // Because the label is allowed to be the same across different
200  // hierarchies, we have to search for all occurrences, and make sure the
201  // referenced sub-object at the found hierarchy is actually the given
202  // object.
203  for (const char* pos = subname; ((pos = strstr(pos, ref.c_str())) != nullptr);
204  pos += ref.size()) {
205  auto sub = std::string(subname, pos + ref.size() - subname);
206  auto sobj = parent->getSubObject(sub.c_str());
207  if (sobj == obj) {
208  sub = subname;
209  sub.replace(pos + 1 - subname, ref.size() - 2, newLabel);
210  return sub;
211  }
212  }
213  return {};
214 }

216 std::vector<std::pair<Property*, std::unique_ptr<Property>>>
217 PropertyLinkBase::updateLabelReferences(App::DocumentObject* obj, const char* newLabel)
218 {
219  std::vector<std::pair<Property*, std::unique_ptr<Property>>> ret;
220  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
221  return ret;
222  }
223  auto it = _LabelMap.find(obj->Label.getStrValue());
224  if (it == _LabelMap.end()) {
225  return ret;
226  }
227  std::string ref("$");
228  ref += obj->Label.getValue();
229  ref += '.';
230  std::vector<PropertyLinkBase*> props;
231  props.reserve(it->second.size());
232  props.insert(props.end(), it->second.begin(), it->second.end());
233  for (auto prop : props) {
234  if (!prop->getContainer()) {
235  continue;
236  }
237  std::unique_ptr<Property> copy(prop->CopyOnLabelChange(obj, ref, newLabel));
238  if (copy) {
239  ret.emplace_back(prop, std::move(copy));
240  }
241  }
242  return ret;
243 }

246 {

248  return {};

251  auto xlink = Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<const PropertyXLink>(prop);
252  if (xlink) {

255  }

272 void PropertyLinkBase::updateElementReferences(DocumentObject* feature, bool reverse)
273 {
274  if (!feature || !feature->getNameInDocument()) {
275  return;
276  }
277  auto it = _ElementRefMap.find(feature);
278  if (it == _ElementRefMap.end()) {
279  return;
280  }
281  std::vector<PropertyLinkBase*> props;
282  props.reserve(it->second.size());
283  props.insert(props.end(), it->second.begin(), it->second.end());
284  for (auto prop : props) {
285  if (prop->getContainer()) {
286  try {
287  prop->updateElementReference(feature, reverse, true);
288  }
289  catch (Base::Exception& e) {
290  e.ReportException();
291  FC_ERR("Failed to update element reference of " << propertyName(prop));
292  }
293  catch (std::exception& e) {
294  FC_ERR("Failed to update element reference of " << propertyName(prop) << ": "
295  << e.what());
296  }
297  }
298  }
299 }

301 void PropertyLinkBase::_registerElementReference(App::DocumentObject* obj,
302  std::string& sub,
303  ShadowSub& shadow)
304 {
305  if (!obj || !obj->getNameInDocument() || sub.empty()) {
306  return;
307  }
308  if (shadow.newName.empty()) {
309  _updateElementReference(nullptr, obj, sub, shadow, false);
310  return;
311  }
312  GeoFeature* geo = nullptr;
313  const char* element = nullptr;
314  ShadowSub elementName;
315  GeoFeature::resolveElement(obj,
316  sub.c_str(),
317  elementName,
318  true,
319  GeoFeature::ElementNameType::Export,
320  nullptr,
321  &element,
322  &geo);
323  if (!geo || !element || !element[0]) {
324  return;
325  }
326 
327  if (_ElementRefs.insert(geo).second) {
328  _ElementRefMap[geo].insert(this);
329  }
330 }

332 class StringGuard
333 {
334 public:
335  explicit StringGuard(char* c)
336  : c(c)
337  {
338  v1 = c[0];
339  v2 = c[1];
340  c[0] = '.';
341  c[1] = 0;
342  }
343  ~StringGuard()
344  {
345  c[0] = v1;
346  c[1] = v2;
347  }
348 
349  char* c;
350  char v1;
351  char v2;
352 };

354 void PropertyLinkBase::restoreLabelReference(const DocumentObject* obj,
355  std::string& subname,
356  ShadowSub* shadow)
357 {
358  std::ostringstream ss;
359  char* sub = &subname[0];
360  char* next = sub;
361  for (char* dot = strchr(next, '.'); dot; next = dot + 1, dot = strchr(next, '.')) {
362  if (dot != next && dot[-1] != '@') {
363  continue;
364  }
365  DocumentObject* sobj;
366  try {
367  StringGuard guard(dot - 1);
368  sobj = obj->getSubObject(subname.c_str());
369  if (!sobj) {
370  FC_ERR("Failed to restore label reference " << obj->getFullName() << '.'
371  << ss.str());
372  return;
373  }
374  }
375  catch (...) {
376  throw;
377  }
378  ss.write(sub, next - sub);
379  ss << '$' << sobj->Label.getStrValue() << '.';
380  sub = dot + 1;
381  }
382  if (sub == subname.c_str()) {
383  return;
384  }
385 
386  size_t count = sub - subname.c_str();
387  const auto& newSub = ss.str();
388  if (shadow && shadow->oldName.size() >= count) {
389  shadow->oldName = newSub + (shadow->oldName.c_str() + count);
390  }
391  if (shadow && shadow->newName.size() >= count) {
392  shadow->newName = newSub + (shadow->newName.c_str() + count);
393  }
394  subname = newSub + sub;
395 }

397 bool PropertyLinkBase::_updateElementReference(DocumentObject* feature,
398  App::DocumentObject* obj,
399  std::string& sub,
400  ShadowSub& shadow,
401  bool reverse,
402  bool notify)
403 {
404  if (!obj || !obj->getNameInDocument()) {
405  return false;
406  }
407  ShadowSub elementName;
408  const char* subname;
409  if (shadow.newName.size()) {
410  subname = shadow.newName.c_str();
411  }
412  else if (shadow.oldName.size()) {
413  subname = shadow.oldName.c_str();
414  }
415  else {
416  subname = sub.c_str();
417  }
418  GeoFeature* geo = nullptr;
419  const char* element = nullptr;
420  auto ret = GeoFeature::resolveElement(obj,
421  subname,
422  elementName,
423  true,
424  GeoFeature::ElementNameType::Export,
425  feature,
426  &element,
427  &geo);
428  if (!ret || !geo || !element || !element[0]) {
429  if (elementName.oldName.size()) {
430  shadow.oldName.swap(elementName.oldName);
431  }
432  return false;
433  }
434 
435  if (_ElementRefs.insert(geo).second) {
436  _ElementRefMap[geo].insert(this);
437  }
438 
439  if (!reverse) {
440  if (elementName.newName.empty()) {
441  shadow.oldName.swap(elementName.oldName);
442  return false;
443  }
444  if (shadow == elementName) {
445  return false;
446  }
447  }
448 
449  bool missing = GeoFeature::hasMissingElement(elementName.oldName.c_str());
450  if (feature == geo && (missing || reverse)) {
451  // If the referenced element is missing, or we are generating element
452  // map for the first time, or we are re-generating the element map due
453  // to version change, i.e. 'reverse', try search by geometry first
454  const char* oldElement = Data::findElementName(shadow.oldName.c_str());
455  if (!Data::hasMissingElement(oldElement)) {
456  const auto& names = geo->searchElementCache(oldElement);
457  if (names.size()) {
458  missing = false;
459  std::string newsub(subname, strlen(subname) - strlen(element));
460  newsub += names.front();
461  GeoFeature::resolveElement(obj,
462  newsub.c_str(),
463  elementName,
464  true,
465  GeoFeature::ElementNameType::Export,
466  feature);
467  const auto& oldName = shadow.newName.size() ? shadow.newName : shadow.oldName;
468  const auto& newName =
469  elementName.newName.size() ? elementName.newName : elementName.oldName;
470  if (oldName != newName) {
471  FC_WARN(propertyName(this)
472  << " auto change element reference " << ret->getFullName() << " "
473  << oldName << " -> " << newName);
474  }
475  }
476  }
477  }
478 
479  if (notify) {
480  aboutToSetValue();
481  }
482 
483  auto updateSub = [&](const std::string& newSub) {
484  if (sub != newSub) {
485  // signalUpdateElementReference(sub, newSub);
486  sub = newSub;
487  }
488  };
489 
490  if (missing) {
491  FC_WARN(propertyName(this)
492  << " missing element reference " << ret->getFullName() << " "
493  << (elementName.newName.size() ? elementName.newName : elementName.oldName));
494  shadow.oldName.swap(elementName.oldName);
495  }
496  else {
497  FC_TRACE(propertyName(this) << " element reference shadow update " << ret->getFullName()
498  << " " << shadow.newName << " -> " << elementName.newName);
499  shadow.swap(elementName);
500  if (shadow.newName.size() && Data::hasMappedElementName(sub.c_str())) {
501  updateSub(shadow.newName);
502  }
503  }
504 
505  if (reverse) {
506  if (shadow.newName.size() && Data::hasMappedElementName(sub.c_str())) {
507  updateSub(shadow.newName);
508  }
509  else {
510  updateSub(shadow.oldName);
511  }
512  return true;
513  }
514  if (missing) {
515  if (sub != shadow.newName) {
516  updateSub(shadow.oldName);
517  }
518  return true;
519  }
520  auto pos2 = shadow.newName.rfind('.');
521  if (pos2 == std::string::npos) {
522  return true;
523  }
524  ++pos2;
525  auto pos = sub.rfind('.');
526  if (pos == std::string::npos) {
527  pos = 0;
528  }
529  else {
530  ++pos;
531  }
532  if (pos == pos2) {
533  if (sub.compare(pos, sub.size() - pos, &shadow.newName[pos2]) != 0) {
534  FC_LOG("element reference update " << sub << " -> " << shadow.newName);
535  std::string newSub(sub);
536  newSub.replace(pos, sub.size() - pos, &shadow.newName[pos2]);
537  updateSub(newSub);
538  }
539  }
540  else if (sub != shadow.oldName) {
541  FC_LOG("element reference update " << sub << " -> " << shadow.oldName);
542  updateSub(shadow.oldName);
543  }
544  return true;
545 }

547 std::pair<DocumentObject*, std::string>
548 PropertyLinkBase::tryReplaceLink(const PropertyContainer* owner,
549  DocumentObject* obj,
550  const DocumentObject* parent,
551  DocumentObject* oldObj,
552  DocumentObject* newObj,
553  const char* subname)
554 {
555  std::pair<DocumentObject*, std::string> res;
556  res.first = 0;
557  if (!obj) {
558  return res;
559  }
560 
561  if (oldObj == obj) {
562  if (owner == parent) {
563  res.first = newObj;
564  if (subname) {
565  res.second = subname;
566  }
567  return res;
568  }
569  return res;
570  }
571  else if (newObj == obj) {
572  // This means the new object is already sub-object of this parent
573  // (consider a case of swapping the tool and base object of the Cut
574  // feature). We'll swap the old and new object.
575  return tryReplaceLink(owner, obj, parent, newObj, oldObj, subname);
576  }
577  if (!subname || !subname[0]) {
578  return res;
579  }
580 
581  App::DocumentObject* prev = obj;
582  std::size_t prevPos = 0;
583  std::string sub = subname;
584  for (auto pos = sub.find('.'); pos != std::string::npos; pos = sub.find('.', pos)) {
585  ++pos;
586  char c = sub[pos];
587  if (c == '.') {
588  continue;
589  }
590  sub[pos] = 0;
591  auto sobj = obj->getSubObject(sub.c_str());
592  sub[pos] = c;
593  if (!sobj) {
594  break;
595  }
596  if (sobj == oldObj) {
597  if (prev == parent) {
598  if (sub[prevPos] == '$') {
599  sub.replace(prevPos + 1, pos - 1 - prevPos, newObj->Label.getValue());
600  }
601  else {
602  sub.replace(prevPos, pos - 1 - prevPos, newObj->getNameInDocument());
603  }
604  res.first = obj;
605  res.second = std::move(sub);
606  return res;
607  }
608  break;
609  }
610  else if (sobj == newObj) {
611  return tryReplaceLink(owner, obj, parent, newObj, oldObj, subname);
612  }
613  else if (prev == parent) {
614  break;
615  }
616  prev = sobj;
617  prevPos = pos;
618  }
619  return res;
620 }

622 std::pair<DocumentObject*, std::vector<std::string>>
623 PropertyLinkBase::tryReplaceLinkSubs(const PropertyContainer* owner,
624  DocumentObject* obj,
625  const DocumentObject* parent,
626  DocumentObject* oldObj,
627  DocumentObject* newObj,
628  const std::vector<std::string>& subs)
629 {
630  std::pair<DocumentObject*, std::vector<std::string>> res;
631  res.first = 0;
632  if (!obj) {
633  return res;
634  }
635 
636  auto r = tryReplaceLink(owner, obj, parent, oldObj, newObj);
637  if (r.first) {
638  res.first = r.first;
639  res.second = subs;
640  return res;
641  }
642  for (auto it = subs.begin(); it != subs.end(); ++it) {
643  auto r = tryReplaceLink(owner, obj, parent, oldObj, newObj, it->c_str());
644  if (r.first) {
645  if (!res.first) {
646  res.first = r.first;
647  res.second.insert(res.second.end(), subs.begin(), it);
648  }
649  res.second.push_back(std::move(r.second));
650  }
651  else if (res.first) {
652  res.second.push_back(*it);
653  }
654  }
655  return res;
656 }

689 void PropertyLink::resetLink()
690 {
691  // in case this property gets dynamically removed
692 #ifndef USE_OLD_DAG
693  // maintain the back link in the DocumentObject class if it is from a document object
694  if (_pcScope != LinkScope::Hidden && _pcLink && getContainer()
695  && getContainer()->isDerivedFrom(App::DocumentObject::getClassTypeId())) {
696  App::DocumentObject* parent = static_cast<DocumentObject*>(getContainer());
697  // before accessing internals make sure the object is not about to be destroyed
698  // otherwise the backlink contains dangling pointers
699  if (!parent->testStatus(ObjectStatus::Destroy)) {
700  if (_pcLink) {
701  _pcLink->_removeBackLink(parent);
702  }
703  }
704  }
705 #endif
706  _pcLink = nullptr;
707 }

709 void PropertyLink::setValue(App::DocumentObject* lValue)
710 {
711  auto parent = dynamic_cast<App::DocumentObject*>(getContainer());
712  if (!testFlag(LinkAllowExternal) && parent && lValue
713  && parent->getDocument() != lValue->getDocument()) {
714  throw Base::ValueError("PropertyLink does not support external object");
715  }
716 
717  aboutToSetValue();
718 #ifndef USE_OLD_DAG
719  // maintain the back link in the DocumentObject class if it is from a document object
720  if (_pcScope != LinkScope::Hidden && parent) {
721  // before accessing internals make sure the object is not about to be destroyed
722  // otherwise the backlink contains dangling pointers
723  if (!parent->testStatus(ObjectStatus::Destroy)) {
724  if (_pcLink) {
725  _pcLink->_removeBackLink(parent);
726  }
727  if (lValue) {
728  lValue->_addBackLink(parent);
729  }
730  }
731  }
732 #endif
733  _pcLink = lValue;
734  hasSetValue();
735 }

775 void PropertyLink::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
776 {
777  // read my element
778  reader.readElement("Link");
779  // get the value of my attribute
780  std::string name = reader.getName(reader.getAttribute("value"));
781 
782  // Property not in a DocumentObject!
783  assert(getContainer()->isDerivedFrom<App::DocumentObject>());
784

786  DocumentObject* parent = static_cast<DocumentObject*>(getContainer());
787

793  "an object was not loaded correctly\n",

795  }
796  }
797  else if (parent == object) {
798  if (reader.isVerbose()) {
799  Base::Console().Warning("Object '%s' links to itself, nullify it\n", name.c_str());
800  }
801  object = nullptr;
802  }
803 
804  setValue(object);
805  }
806  else {
807  setValue(nullptr);
808  }
809 }

1064 void PropertyLinkList::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
1065 {
1066  // read my element
1067  reader.readElement("LinkList");
1068  // get the value of my attribute
1069  int count = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("count");
1070  App::PropertyContainer* container = getContainer();
1071  if (!container) {
1072  throw Base::RuntimeError("Property is not part of a container");
1073  }
1074  if (!container->isDerivedFrom<App::DocumentObject>()) {
1075  std::stringstream str;
1076  str << "Container is not a document object (" << container->getTypeId().getName() << ")";
1077  throw Base::TypeError(str.str());
1078  }
1079 
1080  std::vector<DocumentObject*> values;
1081  values.reserve(count);
1082  for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
1083  reader.readElement("Link");
1084  std::string name = reader.getName(reader.getAttribute("value"));
1085  // In order to do copy/paste it must be allowed to have defined some
1086  // referenced objects in XML which do not exist anymore in the new
1087  // document. Thus, we should silently ignore this.
1088  // Property not in an object!
1089  DocumentObject* father = static_cast<DocumentObject*>(getContainer());
1090  App::Document* document = father->getDocument();
1091  DocumentObject* child = document ? document->getObject(name.c_str()) : nullptr;
1092  if (child) {
1093  values.push_back(child);
1094  }
1095  else if (reader.isVerbose()) {
1096  FC_WARN("Lost link to " << (document ? document->getName() : "") << " " << name
1097  << " while loading, maybe an object was not loaded correctly");
1098  }
1099  }
1100 
1101  reader.readEndElement("LinkList");
1102 
1103  // assignment
1104  setValues(values);
1105 }
1106 
1107 Property* PropertyLinkList::CopyOnLinkReplace(const App::DocumentObject* parent,
1108  App::DocumentObject* oldObj,
1109  App::DocumentObject* newObj) const
1110 {
1111  std::vector<DocumentObject*> links;
1112  bool copied = false;
1113  bool found = false;
1114  for (auto it = _lValueList.begin(); it != _lValueList.end(); ++it) {
1115  auto res = tryReplaceLink(getContainer(), *it, parent, oldObj, newObj);
1116  if (res.first) {
1117  found = true;
1118  if (!copied) {
1119  copied = true;
1120  links.insert(links.end(), _lValueList.begin(), it);
1121  }
1122  links.push_back(res.first);
1123  }
1124  else if (*it == newObj) {
1125  // in case newObj already exists here, we shall remove all existing
1126  // entry, and insert it to take over oldObj's position.
1127  if (!copied) {
1128  copied = true;
1129  links.insert(links.end(), _lValueList.begin(), it);
1130  }
1131  }
1132  else if (copied) {
1133  links.push_back(*it);
1134  }
1135  }
1136  if (!found) {
1137  return nullptr;
1138  }
1139  auto p = new PropertyLinkList();
1140  p->_lValueList = std::move(links);
1141  return p;
1142 }

1166 DocumentObject* PropertyLinkList::find(const char* name, int* pindex) const
1167 {
1168  const int DONT_MAP_UNDER = 10;
1169  if (!name) {
1170  return nullptr;
1171  }
1172  if (_lValueList.size() <= DONT_MAP_UNDER) {
1173  int index = -1;
1174  for (auto obj : _lValueList) {
1175  ++index;
1176  if (obj && obj->getNameInDocument() && boost::equals(name, obj->getNameInDocument())) {
1177  if (pindex) {
1178  *pindex = index;
1179  }
1180  return obj;
1181  }
1182  }
1183  return nullptr;
1184  }
1185  // We're using a map. Do we need to (re)create it?
1186  if (_nameMap.empty() || _nameMap.size() > _lValueList.size()) {
1187  _nameMap.clear();
1188  for (int i = 0; i < (int)_lValueList.size(); ++i) {
1189  auto obj = _lValueList[i];
1190  if (obj && obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1191  _nameMap[obj->getNameInDocument()] = i;
1192  }
1193  }
1194  }
1195  // Now lookup up in that map
1196  auto it = _nameMap.find(name);
1197  if (it == _nameMap.end()) {
1198  return nullptr;
1199  }
1200  if (pindex) {
1201  *pindex = it->second;
1202  }
1203  return _lValueList[it->second];
1204 }
1205 
1206 DocumentObject* PropertyLinkList::findUsingMap(const std::string& name, int* pindex) const
1207 {
1208  if (_nameMap.size() == _lValueList.size()) {
1209  auto it = _nameMap.find(name);
1210  if (it == _nameMap.end()) {
1211  return nullptr;
1212  }
1213  if (pindex) {
1214  *pindex = it->second;
1215  }
1216  return _lValueList[it->second];
1217  }
1218  return find(name.c_str(), pindex);
1219 }

1379 static inline const std::string& getSubNameWithStyle(const std::string& subName,
1380  const PropertyLinkBase::ShadowSub& shadow,
1381  bool newStyle,
1382  std::string& tmp)
1383 {
1384  if (!newStyle) {
1385  if (!shadow.oldName.empty()) {
1386  return shadow.oldName;
1387  }
1388  }
1389  else if (!shadow.newName.empty()) {
1390  if (Data::hasMissingElement(shadow.oldName.c_str())) {
1391  auto pos = shadow.newName.rfind('.');
1392  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
1393  tmp = shadow.newName.substr(0, pos + 1);
1394  tmp += shadow.oldName;
1395  return tmp;
1396  }
1397  }
1398  return shadow.newName;
1399  }
1400  return subName;
1401 }

1439  Py::List list(static_cast<int>(_cSubList.size()));
1440  if (_pcLinkSub) {
1441  tup[0] = Py::asObject(_pcLinkSub->getPyObject());
1442  int i = 0;
1443  for (auto& sub : getSubValues(testFlag(LinkNewElement))) {
1444  list[i++] = Py::String(sub);
1445  }
1446  tup[1] = list;
1447  return Py::new_reference_to(tup);
1448  }
1449  else {
1450  return Py::new_reference_to(Py::None());
1451  }
1452 }

1454 void PropertyLinkSub::setPyObject(PyObject* value)
1455 {
1456  if (PyObject_TypeCheck(value, &(DocumentObjectPy::Type))) {
1457  DocumentObjectPy* pcObject = static_cast<DocumentObjectPy*>(value);
1458  setValue(pcObject->getDocumentObjectPtr());
1459  }
1460  else if (PyTuple_Check(value) || PyList_Check(value)) {
1461  Py::Sequence seq(value);
1462  if (seq.size() == 0) {
1463  setValue(nullptr);
1464  }
1465  else if (seq.size() != 2) {
1466  throw Base::ValueError("Expect input sequence of size 2");
1467  }
1468  else if (PyObject_TypeCheck(seq[0].ptr(), &(DocumentObjectPy::Type))) {
1469  DocumentObjectPy* pcObj = static_cast<DocumentObjectPy*>(seq[0].ptr());
1470  static const char* errMsg =
1471  "type of second element in tuple must be str or sequence of str";
1472  PropertyString propString;
1473  if (seq[1].isString()) {
1474  std::vector<std::string> vals;
1475  propString.setPyObject(seq[1].ptr());
1476  vals.emplace_back(propString.getValue());
1477  setValue(pcObj->getDocumentObjectPtr(), std::move(vals));
1478  }
1479  else if (seq[1].isSequence()) {
1480  Py::Sequence list(seq[1]);
1481  std::vector<std::string> vals(list.size());
1482  unsigned int i = 0;
1483  for (Py::Sequence::iterator it = list.begin(); it != list.end(); ++it, ++i) {
1484  if (!(*it).isString()) {
1485  throw Base::TypeError(errMsg);
1486  }
1487  propString.setPyObject((*it).ptr());
1488  vals[i] = propString.getValue();
1489  }
1490  setValue(pcObj->getDocumentObjectPtr(), std::move(vals));
1491  }
1492  else {
1493  throw Base::TypeError(errMsg);
1494  }
1495  }
1496  else {
1497  std::string error =
1498  std::string("type of first element in tuple must be 'DocumentObject', not ");
1499  error += seq[0].ptr()->ob_type->tp_name;
1500  throw Base::TypeError(error);
1501  }
1502  }
1503  else if (Py_None == value) {
1504  setValue(nullptr);
1505  }
1506  else {
1507  std::string error = std::string(
1508  "type must be 'DocumentObject', 'NoneType' or ('DocumentObject',['String',]) not ");
1509  error += value->ob_type->tp_name;
1510  throw Base::TypeError(error);
1511  }
1512 }

1514 static bool updateLinkReference(App::PropertyLinkBase* prop,
1515  App::DocumentObject* feature,
1516  bool reverse,
1517  bool notify,
1518  App::DocumentObject* link,
1519  std::vector<std::string>& subs,
1520  std::vector<int>& mapped,
1521  std::vector<PropertyLinkBase::ShadowSub>& shadows)
1522 {
1523  if (!feature) {
1524  shadows.clear();
1525  prop->unregisterElementReference();
1526  }
1527  shadows.resize(subs.size());
1528  if (!link || !link->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1529  return false;
1530  }
1531  auto owner = dynamic_cast<DocumentObject*>(prop->getContainer());
1532  if (owner && owner->isRestoring()) {
1533  return false;
1534  }
1535  int i = 0;
1536  bool touched = false;
1537  for (auto& sub : subs) {
1538  if (prop->_updateElementReference(feature,
1539  link,
1540  sub,
1541  shadows[i++],
1542  reverse,
1543  notify && !touched)) {
1544  touched = true;
1545  }
1546  }
1547  if (!touched) {
1548  return false;
1549  }
1550  for (int idx : mapped) {
1551  if (idx < (int)subs.size() && !shadows[idx].newName.empty()) {
1552  subs[idx] = shadows[idx].newName;
1553  }
1554  }
1555  mapped.clear();
1556  if (owner && feature) {
1557  owner->onUpdateElementReference(prop);
1558  }
1559  return true;
1560 }

1607 std::string
1608 PropertyLinkBase::importSubName(Base::XMLReader& reader, const char* sub, bool& restoreLabel)
1609 {
1610  if (!reader.doNameMapping()) {
1611  return sub;
1612  }
1613  std::ostringstream str;
1614  for (const char* dot = strchr(sub, '.'); dot; sub = dot + 1, dot = strchr(sub, '.')) {
1615  size_t count = dot - sub;
1616  const char* tail = ".";
1617  if (count && dot[-1] == '@') {
1618  // tail=='@' means we are exporting a label reference. So retain
1619  // this marker so that the label can be restored in afterRestore().
1620  tail = "@.";
1621  --count;
1622  restoreLabel = true;
1623  }
1624  str << reader.getName(std::string(sub, count).c_str()) << tail;
1625  }
1626  str << sub;
1627  return str.str();
1628 }
1629 
1630 const char* PropertyLinkBase::exportSubName(std::string& output,
1631  const App::DocumentObject* obj,
1632  const char* sub,
1633  bool first_obj)
1634 {
1635  std::ostringstream str;
1636  const char* res = sub;
1637 
1638  if (!sub || !sub[0]) {
1639  return res;
1640  }
1641 
1642  bool touched = false;
1643  if (first_obj) {
1644  auto dot = strchr(sub, '.');
1645  if (!dot) {
1646  return res;
1647  }
1648  const char* hash;
1649  for (hash = sub; hash < dot && *hash != '#'; ++hash) {}
1650  App::Document* doc = nullptr;
1651  if (*hash == '#') {
1652  doc = GetApplication().getDocument(std::string(sub, hash - sub).c_str());
1653  }
1654  else {
1655  hash = nullptr;
1656  if (obj && obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1657  doc = obj->getDocument();
1658  }
1659  }
1660  if (!doc) {
1661  FC_ERR("Failed to get document for the first object in " << sub);
1662  return res;
1663  }
1664  obj = doc->getObject(std::string(sub, dot - sub).c_str());
1665  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1666  return res;
1667  }
1668  if (hash) {
1669  if (!obj->isExporting()) {
1670  str << doc->getName() << '#';
1671  }
1672  sub = hash + 1;
1673  }
1674  }
1675  else if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1676  return res;
1677  }
1678 
1679  for (const char* dot = strchr(sub, '.'); dot; sub = dot + 1, dot = strchr(sub, '.')) {
1680  // name with trailing '.'
1681  auto name = std::string(sub, dot - sub + 1);
1682  if (first_obj) {
1683  first_obj = false;
1684  }
1685  else {
1686  obj = obj->getSubObject(name.c_str());
1687  }
1688  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1689  FC_WARN("missing sub object '" << name << "' in '" << sub << "'");
1690  break;
1691  }
1692  if (obj->isExporting()) {
1693  if (name[0] == '$') {
1694  if (name.compare(1, name.size() - 2, obj->Label.getValue()) != 0) {
1695  str << obj->getExportName(true) << "@.";
1696  touched = true;
1697  continue;
1698  }
1699  }
1700  else if (name.compare(0, name.size() - 1, obj->getNameInDocument()) == 0) {
1701  str << obj->getExportName(true) << '.';
1702  touched = true;
1703  continue;
1704  }
1705  }
1706  str << name;
1707  }
1708  if (!touched) {
1709  return res;
1710  }
1711  str << sub;
1712  output = str.str();
1713  return output.c_str();
1714 }

1716 App::DocumentObject* PropertyLinkBase::tryImport(const App::Document* doc,
1717  const App::DocumentObject* obj,
1718  const std::map<std::string, std::string>& nameMap)
1719 {
1720  if (doc && obj && obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1721  auto it = nameMap.find(obj->getExportName(true));
1722  if (it != nameMap.end()) {
1723  obj = doc->getObject(it->second.c_str());
1724  if (!obj) {
1725  FC_THROWM(Base::RuntimeError, "Cannot find import object " << it->second);
1726  }
1727  }
1728  }
1729  return const_cast<DocumentObject*>(obj);
1730 }
1731 
1732 std::string PropertyLinkBase::tryImportSubName(const App::DocumentObject* obj,
1733  const char* _subname,
1734  const App::Document* doc,
1735  const std::map<std::string, std::string>& nameMap)
1736 {
1737  if (!doc || !obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1738  return {};
1739  }
1740 
1741  std::ostringstream ss;
1742  std::string subname(_subname);
1743  char* sub = &subname[0];
1744  char* next = sub;
1745  for (char* dot = strchr(next, '.'); dot; next = dot + 1, dot = strchr(next, '.')) {
1746  StringGuard guard(dot);
1747  auto sobj = obj->getSubObject(subname.c_str());
1748  if (!sobj) {
1749  FC_ERR("Failed to restore label reference " << obj->getFullName() << '.' << subname);
1750  return {};
1751  }
1752  dot[0] = 0;
1753  if (next[0] == '$') {
1754  if (strcmp(next + 1, sobj->Label.getValue()) != 0) {
1755  continue;
1756  }
1757  }
1758  else if (strcmp(next, sobj->getNameInDocument()) != 0) {
1759  continue;
1760  }
1761  auto it = nameMap.find(sobj->getExportName(true));
1762  if (it == nameMap.end()) {
1763  continue;
1764  }
1765  auto imported = doc->getObject(it->second.c_str());
1766  if (!imported) {
1767  FC_THROWM(RuntimeError, "Failed to find imported object " << it->second);
1768  }
1769  ss.write(sub, next - sub);
1770  if (next[0] == '$') {
1771  ss << '$' << imported->Label.getStrValue() << '.';
1772  }
1773  else {
1774  ss << it->second << '.';
1775  }
1776  sub = dot + 1;
1777  }
1778  if (sub != subname.c_str()) {
1779  return ss.str();
1780  }
1781  return {};
1782 }

1784 void PropertyLinkBase::_getLinksTo(std::vector<App::ObjectIdentifier>& identifiers,
1785  App::DocumentObject* obj,
1786  const char* subname,
1787  const std::vector<std::string>& subs,
1788  const std::vector<PropertyLinkBase::ShadowSub>& shadows) const
1789 {
1790  if (!subname) {
1791  identifiers.emplace_back(*this);
1792  return;
1793  }
1794  App::SubObjectT objT(obj, subname);
1795  auto subObject = objT.getSubObject();
1796  auto subElement = objT.getOldElementName();
1797 
1798  int i = -1;
1799  for (const auto& sub : subs) {
1800  ++i;
1801  if (sub == subname) {
1802  identifiers.emplace_back(*this);
1803  return;
1804  }
1805  if (!subObject) {
1806  continue;
1807  }
1808  // After above, there is a subobject and the subname doesn't match our current entry
1809  App::SubObjectT sobjT(obj, sub.c_str());
1810  if (sobjT.getSubObject() == subObject && sobjT.getOldElementName() == subElement) {
1811  identifiers.emplace_back(*this);
1812  return;
1813  }
1814  // And the oldElementName ( short, I.E. "Edge5" ) doesn't match.
1815  if (i < (int)shadows.size()) {
1816  const auto& [shadowNewName, shadowOldName] = shadows[i];
1817  if (shadowNewName == subname || shadowOldName == subname) {
1818  identifiers.emplace_back(*this);
1819  return;
1820  }
1821  if (!subObject) {
1822  continue;
1823  }
1824  App::SubObjectT shadowobjT(obj,
1825  shadowNewName.empty() ? shadowOldName.c_str()
1826  : shadowNewName.c_str());
1827  if (shadowobjT.getSubObject() == subObject
1828  && shadowobjT.getOldElementName() == subElement) {
1829  identifiers.emplace_back(*this);
1830  return;
1831  }
1832  }
1833  }
1834 }

1836 #define ATTR_SHADOWED "shadowed"
1837 #define ATTR_SHADOW "shadow"
1838 #define ATTR_MAPPED "mapped"
1839 
1840 #define IGNORE_SHADOW false
1841 
1842 void PropertyLinkSub::Save(Base::Writer& writer) const
1843 {
1844  assert(_cSubList.size() == _ShadowSubList.size());
1845 
1846  std::string internal_name;
1847  // it can happen that the object is still alive but is not part of the document anymore and thus
1848  // returns 0
1849  if (_pcLinkSub && _pcLinkSub->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1850  internal_name = _pcLinkSub->getExportName();
1851  }
1852  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "<LinkSub value=\"" << internal_name << "\" count=\""
1853  << _cSubList.size();
1854  writer.Stream() << "\">" << std::endl;
1855  writer.incInd();
1856  auto owner = dynamic_cast<DocumentObject*>(getContainer());
1857  bool exporting = owner && owner->isExporting();
1858  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < _cSubList.size(); i++) {
1859  const auto& shadow = _ShadowSubList[i];
1860  // shadow.oldName stores the old style element name. For backward
1861  // compatibility reason, we shall store the old name into attribute
1862  // 'value' whenever possible.
1863  const auto& sub = shadow.oldName.empty() ? _cSubList[i] : shadow.oldName;
1864  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "<Sub value=\"";
1865  if (exporting) {
1866  std::string exportName;
1867  writer.Stream() << encodeAttribute(exportSubName(exportName, _pcLinkSub, sub.c_str()));
1868  if (!shadow.oldName.empty() && shadow.newName == _cSubList[i]) {
1869  writer.Stream() << "\" " ATTR_MAPPED "=\"1";
1870  }
1871  }
1872  else {
1873  writer.Stream() << encodeAttribute(sub);
1874  if (!_cSubList[i].empty()) {
1875  if (sub != _cSubList[i]) {
1876  // Stores the actual value that is shadowed. For new version FC,
1877  // we will restore this shadowed value instead.
1878  writer.Stream() << "\" " ATTR_SHADOWED "=\"" << encodeAttribute(_cSubList[i]);
1879  }
1880  else if (!shadow.newName.empty()) {
1881  // Here means the user set value is old style element name.
1882  // We shall then store the shadow somewhere else.
1883  writer.Stream() << "\" " ATTR_SHADOW "=\"" << encodeAttribute(shadow.newName);
1884  }
1885  }
1886  }
1887  writer.Stream() << "\"/>" << endl;
1888  }
1889  writer.decInd();
1890  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "</LinkSub>" << endl;
1891 }

1893 void PropertyLinkSub::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
1894 {
1895  // read my element
1896  reader.readElement("LinkSub");
1897  // get the values of my attributes
1898  std::string name = reader.getName(reader.getAttribute("value"));
1899  int count = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("count");
1900 
1901  // Property not in a DocumentObject!
1902  assert(getContainer()->isDerivedFrom<App::DocumentObject>());
1903  App::Document* document = static_cast<DocumentObject*>(getContainer())->getDocument();
1904 
1905  DocumentObject* pcObject = nullptr;
1906  if (!name.empty()) {
1907  pcObject = document ? document->getObject(name.c_str()) : nullptr;
1908  if (!pcObject) {
1909  if (reader.isVerbose()) {
1910  FC_WARN("Lost link to "
1911  << name << " while loading, maybe an object was not loaded correctly");
1912  }
1913  }
1914  }
1915 
1916  std::vector<int> mapped;
1917  std::vector<std::string> values(count);
1918  std::vector<ShadowSub> shadows(count);
1919  bool restoreLabel = false;
1920  // Sub may store '.' separated object names, so be aware of the possible mapping when import
1921  for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
1922  reader.readElement("Sub");
1923  shadows[i].oldName = importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute("value"), restoreLabel);
1924  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_SHADOWED) && !IGNORE_SHADOW) {
1925  values[i] = shadows[i].newName =
1926  importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute(ATTR_SHADOWED), restoreLabel);
1927  }
1928  else {
1929  values[i] = shadows[i].oldName;
1930  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_SHADOW) && !IGNORE_SHADOW) {
1931  shadows[i].newName =
1932  importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute(ATTR_SHADOW), restoreLabel);
1933  }
1934  }
1935  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_MAPPED)) {
1936  mapped.push_back(i);
1937  }
1938  }
1939  setFlag(LinkRestoreLabel, restoreLabel);
1940 
1941  reader.readEndElement("LinkSub");
1942 
1943  if (pcObject) {
1944  setValue(pcObject, std::move(values), std::move(shadows));
1945  _mapped = std::move(mapped);
1946  }
1947  else {
1948  setValue(nullptr);
1949  }
1950 }

1952 template<class Func, class... Args>
1953 std::vector<std::string> updateLinkSubs(const App::DocumentObject* obj,
1954  const std::vector<std::string>& subs,
1955  Func* f,
1956  Args&&... args)
1957 {
1958  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1959  return {};
1960  }
1961 
1962  std::vector<std::string> res;
1963  for (auto it = subs.begin(); it != subs.end(); ++it) {
1964  const auto& sub = *it;
1965  auto new_sub = (*f)(obj, sub.c_str(), std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1966  if (new_sub.size()) {
1967  if (res.empty()) {
1968  res.reserve(subs.size());
1969  res.insert(res.end(), subs.begin(), it);
1970  }
1971  res.push_back(std::move(new_sub));
1972  }
1973  else if (!res.empty()) {
1974  res.push_back(sub);
1975  }
1976  }
1977  return res;
1978 }

2098 static App::DocumentObject*
2099 adjustLinkSubs(App::PropertyLinkBase* prop,
2100  const std::set<App::DocumentObject*>& inList,
2101  App::DocumentObject* link,
2102  std::vector<std::string>& subs,
2103  std::map<App::DocumentObject*, std::vector<std::string>>* links = nullptr)
2104 {
2105  App::DocumentObject* newLink = nullptr;
2106  for (auto& sub : subs) {
2107  size_t pos = sub.find('.');
2108  for (; pos != std::string::npos; pos = sub.find('.', pos + 1)) {
2109  auto sobj = link->getSubObject(sub.substr(0, pos + 1).c_str());
2110  if (!sobj
2111  || (!prop->testFlag(PropertyLinkBase::LinkAllowExternal)
2112  && sobj->getDocument() != link->getDocument())) {
2113  pos = std::string::npos;
2114  break;
2115  }
2116  if (!newLink) {
2117  if (inList.count(sobj)) {
2118  continue;
2119  }
2120  newLink = sobj;
2121  if (links) {
2122  (*links)[sobj].push_back(sub.substr(pos + 1));
2123  }
2124  else {
2125  sub = sub.substr(pos + 1);
2126  }
2127  }
2128  else if (links) {
2129  (*links)[sobj].push_back(sub.substr(pos + 1));
2130  }
2131  else if (sobj == newLink) {
2132  sub = sub.substr(pos + 1);
2133  }
2134  break;
2135  }
2136  if (pos == std::string::npos) {
2137  return nullptr;
2138  }
2139  }
2140  return newLink;
2141 }

2143 bool PropertyLinkSub::adjustLink(const std::set<App::DocumentObject*>& inList)
2144 {
2145  if (_pcScope == LinkScope::Hidden) {
2146  return false;
2147  }
2148  if (!_pcLinkSub || !_pcLinkSub->isAttachedToDocument() || !inList.count(_pcLinkSub)) {
2149  return false;
2150  }
2151  auto subs = _cSubList;
2152  auto link = adjustLinkSubs(this, inList, _pcLinkSub, subs);
2153  if (link) {
2154  setValue(link, std::move(subs));
2155  return true;
2156  }
2157  return false;
2158 }

2426 void PropertyLinkSubList::addValue(App::DocumentObject* obj,
2427  const std::vector<std::string>& subs,
2428  bool reset)
2429 {
2430  auto parent = Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<App::DocumentObject>(getContainer());
2431  verifyObject(obj, parent);
2432 
2433 #ifndef USE_OLD_DAG
2434  // maintain backlinks.
2435  if (parent) {
2436  // before accessing internals make sure the object is not about to be destroyed
2437  // otherwise the backlink contains dangling pointers
2438  if (!parent->testStatus(ObjectStatus::Destroy) && _pcScope != LinkScope::Hidden) {
2439  //_lValueList can contain items multiple times, but we trust the document
2440  // object to ensure that this works
2441  if (reset) {
2442  for (auto* value : _lValueList) {
2443  if (value && value == obj) {
2444  value->_removeBackLink(parent);
2445  }
2446  }
2447  }
2448 
2449  // maintain backlinks. lValue can contain items multiple times, but we trust the
2450  // document object to ensure that the backlink is only added once
2451  if (obj) {
2452  obj->_addBackLink(parent);
2453  }
2454  }
2455  }
2456 #endif
2457 
2458  std::vector<DocumentObject*> valueList;
2459  std::vector<std::string> subList;
2460 
2461  if (reset) {
2462  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < _lValueList.size(); i++) {
2463  if (_lValueList[i] != obj) {
2464  valueList.push_back(_lValueList[i]);
2465  subList.push_back(_lSubList[i]);
2466  }
2467  }
2468  }
2469  else {
2470  valueList = _lValueList;
2471  subList = _lSubList;
2472  }
2473 
2474  std::size_t size = subs.size();
2475  if (size == 0) {
2476  if (obj) {
2477  valueList.push_back(obj);
2478  subList.emplace_back();
2479  }
2480  }
2481  else if (obj) {
2482  subList.insert(subList.end(), subs.begin(), subs.end());
2483  valueList.insert(valueList.end(), size, obj);
2484  }
2485 
2486  aboutToSetValue();
2487  _lValueList = valueList;
2488  _lSubList = subList;
2489  updateElementReference(nullptr);
2490  checkLabelReferences(_lSubList);
2491  hasSetValue();
2492 }

2646 void PropertyLinkSubList::setPyObject(PyObject* value)
2647 {
2648  try { // try PropertyLinkSub syntax
2649  PropertyLinkSub dummy;
2650  dummy.setPyObject(value);
2651  this->setValue(dummy.getValue(), dummy.getSubValues());
2652  return;
2653  }
2654  catch (...) {
2655  }
2656  try {
2657  // try PropertyLinkList syntax
2658  PropertyLinkList dummy;
2659  dummy.setPyObject(value);
2660  const auto& values = dummy.getValues();
2661  std::vector<std::string> subs(values.size());
2662  this->setValues(values, subs);
2663  return;
2664  }
2665  catch (...) {
2666  }
2667 
2668  static const char* errMsg =
2669  "Expects sequence of items of type DocObj, (DocObj,SubName), or (DocObj, (SubName,...))";
2670 
2671  if (!PyTuple_Check(value) && !PyList_Check(value)) {
2672  throw Base::TypeError(errMsg);
2673  }
2674 
2675  Py::Sequence list(value);
2676  Py::Sequence::size_type size = list.size();
2677 
2678  std::vector<DocumentObject*> values;
2679  values.reserve(size);
2680  std::vector<std::string> SubNames;
2681  SubNames.reserve(size);
2682  for (Py::Sequence::size_type i = 0; i < size; i++) {
2683  Py::Object item = list[i];
2684  if ((item.isTuple() || item.isSequence()) && PySequence_Size(*item) == 2) {
2685  Py::Sequence seq(item);
2686  if (PyObject_TypeCheck(seq[0].ptr(), &(DocumentObjectPy::Type))) {
2687  auto obj = static_cast<DocumentObjectPy*>(seq[0].ptr())->getDocumentObjectPtr();
2688  PropertyString propString;
2689  if (seq[1].isString()) {
2690  values.push_back(obj);
2691  propString.setPyObject(seq[1].ptr());
2692  SubNames.emplace_back(propString.getValue());
2693  }
2694  else if (seq[1].isSequence()) {
2695  Py::Sequence list(seq[1]);
2696  for (Py::Sequence::iterator it = list.begin(); it != list.end(); ++it) {
2697  if (!(*it).isString()) {
2698  throw Base::TypeError(errMsg);
2699  }
2700  values.push_back(obj);
2701  propString.setPyObject((*it).ptr());
2702  SubNames.emplace_back(propString.getValue());
2703  }
2704  }
2705  else {
2706  throw Base::TypeError(errMsg);
2707  }
2708  }
2709  }
2710  else if (PyObject_TypeCheck(*item, &(DocumentObjectPy::Type))) {
2711  DocumentObjectPy* pcObj;
2712  pcObj = static_cast<DocumentObjectPy*>(*item);
2713  values.push_back(pcObj->getDocumentObjectPtr());
2714  SubNames.emplace_back();
2715  }
2716  else {
2717  throw Base::TypeError(errMsg);
2718  }
2719  }
2720  setValues(values, SubNames);
2721 }

2752  return;

2759  obj,
2760  sub,

2762  reverse,

2764  touched = true;
2765  }
2766  }

2768  return;

2776  _lSubList[idx] = _ShadowSubList[idx].newName;
2777  }
2778  else {
2779  mapped.push_back(idx);
2780  }
2781  }
2782  }
2783  _mapped.swap(mapped);

2786  }

2852 void PropertyLinkSubList::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
2853 {
2854  // read my element
2855  reader.readElement("LinkSubList");
2856  // get the value of my attribute
2857  int count = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("count");
2858 
2859  std::vector<DocumentObject*> values;
2860  values.reserve(count);
2861  std::vector<std::string> SubNames;
2862  SubNames.reserve(count);
2863  std::vector<ShadowSub> shadows;
2864  shadows.reserve(count);
2865  DocumentObject* father = dynamic_cast<DocumentObject*>(getContainer());
2866  App::Document* document = father ? father->getDocument() : nullptr;
2867  std::vector<int> mapped;
2868  bool restoreLabel = false;
2869  for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
2870  reader.readElement("Link");
2871  std::string name = reader.getName(reader.getAttribute("obj"));
2872  // In order to do copy/paste it must be allowed to have defined some
2873  // referenced objects in XML which do not exist anymore in the new
2874  // document. Thus, we should silently ignore this.
2875  // Property not in an object!
2876  DocumentObject* child = document ? document->getObject(name.c_str()) : nullptr;
2877  if (child) {
2878  values.push_back(child);
2879  shadows.emplace_back();
2880  auto& shadow = shadows.back();
2881  shadow.oldName = importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute("sub"), restoreLabel);
2882  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_SHADOWED) && !IGNORE_SHADOW) {
2883  shadow.newName =
2884  importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute(ATTR_SHADOWED), restoreLabel);
2885  SubNames.push_back(shadow.newName);
2886  }
2887  else {
2888  SubNames.push_back(shadow.oldName);
2889  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_SHADOW) && !IGNORE_SHADOW) {
2890  shadow.newName =
2891  importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute(ATTR_SHADOW), restoreLabel);
2892  }
2893  }
2894  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_MAPPED)) {
2895  mapped.push_back(i);
2896  }
2897  }
2898  else if (reader.isVerbose()) {
2899  Base::Console().Warning("Lost link to '%s' while loading, maybe "
2900  "an object was not loaded correctly\n",
2901  name.c_str());
2902  }
2903  }
2904  setFlag(LinkRestoreLabel, restoreLabel);
2905 
2906  reader.readEndElement("LinkSubList");
2907 
2908  // assignment
2909  setValues(values, SubNames, std::move(shadows));
2910  _mapped.swap(mapped);
2911 }

3035 Property* PropertyLinkSubList::CopyOnLinkReplace(const App::DocumentObject* parent,
3036  App::DocumentObject* oldObj,
3037  App::DocumentObject* newObj) const
3038 {
3039  std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> values;
3040  std::vector<std::string> subs;
3041  auto itSub = _lSubList.begin();
3042  std::vector<size_t> positions;
3043  for (auto itValue = _lValueList.begin(); itValue != _lValueList.end(); ++itValue, ++itSub) {
3044  auto value = *itValue;
3045  const auto& sub = *itSub;
3046  if (!value || !value->isAttachedToDocument()) {
3047  if (!values.empty()) {
3048  values.push_back(value);
3049  subs.push_back(sub);
3050  }
3051  continue;
3052  }
3053  auto res = tryReplaceLink(getContainer(), value, parent, oldObj, newObj, sub.c_str());
3054  if (res.first) {
3055  if (values.empty()) {
3056  values.reserve(_lValueList.size());
3057  values.insert(values.end(), _lValueList.begin(), itValue);
3058  subs.reserve(_lSubList.size());
3059  subs.insert(subs.end(), _lSubList.begin(), itSub);
3060  }
3061  if (res.first == newObj) {
3062  // check for duplication
3063  auto itS = subs.begin();
3064  for (auto itV = values.begin(); itV != values.end();) {
3065  if (*itV == res.first && *itS == res.second) {
3066  itV = values.erase(itV);
3067  itS = subs.erase(itS);
3068  }
3069  else {
3070  ++itV;
3071  ++itS;
3072  }
3073  }
3074  positions.push_back(values.size());
3075  }
3076  values.push_back(res.first);
3077  subs.push_back(std::move(res.second));
3078  }
3079  else if (!values.empty()) {
3080  bool duplicate = false;
3081  if (value == newObj) {
3082  for (auto pos : positions) {
3083  if (sub == subs[pos]) {
3084  duplicate = true;
3085  break;
3086  }
3087  }
3088  }
3089  if (!duplicate) {
3090  values.push_back(value);
3091  subs.push_back(sub);
3092  }
3093  }
3094  }
3095  if (values.empty()) {
3096  return nullptr;
3097  }
3098  std::unique_ptr<PropertyLinkSubList> p(new PropertyLinkSubList);
3099  p->_lValueList = std::move(values);
3100  p->_lSubList = std::move(subs);
3101  return p.release();
3102 }

3486  void attach(Document* doc)
3487  {
3488  assert(!pcDoc);
3489  pcDoc = doc;
3490  FC_LOG("attaching " << doc->getName() << ", " << doc->getFileName());
3491  std::map<App::PropertyLinkBase*, std::vector<App::PropertyXLink*>> parentLinks;
3492  for (auto it = links.begin(), itNext = it; it != links.end(); it = itNext) {
3493  ++itNext;
3494  auto link = *it;
3495  if (link->_pcLink) {
3496  continue;
3497  }
3498  if (link->parentProp) {
3499  parentLinks[link->parentProp].push_back(link);
3500  continue;
3501  }
3502  auto obj = doc->getObject(link->objectName.c_str());
3503  if (obj) {
3504  link->restoreLink(obj);
3505  }
3506  else if (doc->testStatus(App::Document::PartialDoc)) {
3507  App::GetApplication().addPendingDocument(doc->FileName.getValue(),
3508  link->objectName.c_str(),
3509  false);
3510  FC_WARN("reloading partial document '" << doc->FileName.getValue()
3511  << "' due to object " << link->objectName);
3512  }
3513  else {
3514  FC_WARN("object '" << link->objectName << "' not found in document '"
3515  << doc->getName() << "'");
3516  }
3517  }
3518  for (auto& v : parentLinks) {
3519  v.first->setFlag(PropertyLinkBase::LinkRestoring);
3520  v.first->aboutToSetValue();
3521  for (auto link : v.second) {
3522  auto obj = doc->getObject(link->objectName.c_str());
3523  if (obj) {
3524  link->restoreLink(obj);
3525  }
3526  else if (doc->testStatus(App::Document::PartialDoc)) {
3527  App::GetApplication().addPendingDocument(doc->FileName.getValue(),
3528  link->objectName.c_str(),
3529  false);
3530  FC_WARN("reloading partial document '"
3531  << doc->FileName.getValue() << "' due to object " << link->objectName);
3532  }
3533  else {
3534  FC_WARN("object '" << link->objectName << "' not found in document '"
3535  << doc->getName() << "'");
3536  }
3537  }
3538  v.first->hasSetValue();
3539  v.first->setFlag(PropertyLinkBase::LinkRestoring, false);
3540  }
3541  }

3574  void slotSaveDocument(const App::Document& doc)
3575  {
3576  if (!pcDoc) {
3577  slotFinishRestoreDocument(doc);
3578  return;
3579  }
3580  if (&doc != pcDoc) {
3581  return;
3582  }
3583 
3584  QFileInfo info(myPos->first);
3585  QString path(info.absoluteFilePath());
3586  const char* filename = doc.getFileName();
3587  QString docPath(getFullPath(filename));
3588 
3589  if (path.isEmpty() || path != docPath) {
3590  FC_LOG("document '" << doc.getName() << "' path changed");
3591  auto me = shared_from_this();
3592  auto ret = _DocInfoMap.insert(std::make_pair(docPath, me));
3593  if (!ret.second) {
3594  // is that even possible?
3595  FC_WARN("document '" << doc.getName() << "' path exists, detach");
3596  slotDeleteDocument(doc);
3597  return;
3598  }
3599  _DocInfoMap.erase(myPos);
3600  myPos = ret.first;
3601 
3602  std::set<PropertyXLink*> tmp;
3603  tmp.swap(links);
3604  for (auto link : tmp) {
3605  auto owner = static_cast<DocumentObject*>(link->getContainer());
3606  // adjust file path for each PropertyXLink
3607  DocInfo::get(filename, owner->getDocument(), link, link->objectName.c_str());
3608  }
3609  }
3610 
3611  // time stamp changed, touch the linking document.
3612  std::set<Document*> docs;
3613  for (auto link : links) {
3614  auto linkdoc = static_cast<DocumentObject*>(link->getContainer())->getDocument();
3615  auto ret = docs.insert(linkdoc);

3618  FC_LOG("touch document " << linkdoc->getName() << " on time stamp change of "

3620  linkdoc->Comment.touch();

3625  void slotDeleteDocument(const App::Document& doc)
3626  {
3627  for (auto it = links.begin(), itNext = it; it != links.end(); it = itNext) {
3628  ++itNext;
3629  auto link = *it;
3630  auto obj = dynamic_cast<DocumentObject*>(link->getContainer());
3631  if (obj && obj->getDocument() == &doc) {
3632  links.erase(it);
3633  // must call unlink here, so that PropertyLink::resetLink can
3634  // remove back link before the owner object is marked as being
3635  // destroyed
3636  link->unlink();
3637  }
3638  }
3639  if (links.empty()) {
3640  deinit();
3641  return;
3642  }
3643  if (pcDoc != &doc) {
3644  return;
3645  }
3646  std::map<App::PropertyLinkBase*, std::vector<App::PropertyXLink*>> parentLinks;
3647  for (auto link : links) {
3648  link->setFlag(PropertyLinkBase::LinkDetached);
3649  if (link->parentProp) {
3650  parentLinks[link->parentProp].push_back(link);
3651  }
3652  else {
3653  parentLinks[nullptr].push_back(link);
3654  }
3655  }
3656  for (auto& v : parentLinks) {
3657  if (v.first) {
3658  v.first->setFlag(PropertyLinkBase::LinkDetached);
3659  v.first->aboutToSetValue();
3660  }
3661  for (auto l : v.second) {
3662  l->detach();
3663  }
3664  if (v.first) {
3665  v.first->hasSetValue();
3666  v.first->setFlag(PropertyLinkBase::LinkDetached, false);
3667  }
3668  }
3669  pcDoc = nullptr;
3670  }

3683  static void breakLinks(App::DocumentObject* obj, bool clear)
3684  {
3685  auto doc = obj->getDocument();
3686  for (auto itD = _DocInfoMap.begin(), itDNext = itD; itD != _DocInfoMap.end();
3687  itD = itDNext) {
3688  ++itDNext;
3689  auto docInfo = itD->second;
3690  if (docInfo->pcDoc != doc) {
3691  continue;
3692  }
3693  auto& links = docInfo->links;
3694  std::set<PropertyLinkBase*> parentLinks;
3695  for (auto it = links.begin(), itNext = it; it != links.end(); it = itNext) {
3696  ++itNext;
3697  auto link = *it;
3698  if (link->_pcLink != obj && !(clear && link->getContainer() == obj)) {
3699  continue;
3700  }
3701  if (link->parentProp) {
3702  parentLinks.insert(link->parentProp);
3703  }
3704  else {
3705  link->breakLink(obj, clear);
3706  }
3707  }
3708  for (auto link : parentLinks) {
3709  link->breakLink(obj, clear);
3710  }
3711  }
3712  }
3713 };

3868 void PropertyXLink::setValue(App::DocumentObject* lValue,
3869  std::vector<std::string>&& subs,

3871 {

4058  }

4060  ss << std::endl << "Linked file: " << filePath;
4061  }
4062  *msg = ss.str();
4063  }
4064  return 2;
4065  }
4066  if (!docInfo->pcDoc || stamp == docInfo->pcDoc->LastModifiedDate.getValue()) {
4067  return 0;
4068  }
4069 
4070  if (msg) {
4071  std::ostringstream ss;
4072  ss << "Time stamp changed on link " << _pcLink->getFullName();
4073  *msg = ss.str();
4074  }

4122 void PropertyXLink::Save(Base::Writer& writer) const
4123 {
4124  auto owner = dynamic_cast<const DocumentObject*>(getContainer());
4125  if (!owner || !owner->getDocument()) {
4126  return;
4127  }
4128 
4129  assert(_SubList.size() == _ShadowSubList.size());
4130 
4131  auto exporting = owner->isExporting();
4132  if (_pcLink && exporting && _pcLink->isExporting()) {
4133  // this means, we are exporting the owner and the linked object together.
4134  // Lets save the export name
4135  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "<XLink name=\"" << _pcLink->getExportName();
4136  }
4137  else {
4138  const char* path = filePath.c_str();
4139  std::string _path;
4140  if (exporting) {
4141  // Here means we are exporting the owner but not exporting the
4142  // linked object. Try to use absolute file path for easy transition
4143  // into document at different directory
4144  if (docInfo) {
4145  _path = docInfo->filePath();
4146  }
4147  else {
4148  auto pDoc = owner->getDocument();
4149  const char* docPath = pDoc->getFileName();
4150  if (docPath && docPath[0]) {
4151  if (!filePath.empty()) {
4152  _path = DocInfo::getDocPath(filePath.c_str(), pDoc, false);
4153  }
4154  else {
4155  _path = docPath;
4156  }
4157  }
4158  else {
4159  FC_WARN("PropertyXLink export without saving the document");
4160  }
4161  }
4162  if (!_path.empty()) {
4163  path = _path.c_str();
4164  }
4165  }
4166  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "<XLink file=\"" << encodeAttribute(path)
4167  << "\" stamp=\""
4168  << (docInfo && docInfo->pcDoc ? docInfo->pcDoc->LastModifiedDate.getValue()
4169  : "")
4170  << "\" name=\"" << objectName;
4171  }
4172 
4173  if (testFlag(LinkAllowPartial)) {
4174  writer.Stream() << "\" partial=\"1";
4175  }
4176 
4177  if (_SubList.empty()) {
4178  writer.Stream() << "\"/>" << std::endl;
4179  }
4180  else if (_SubList.size() == 1) {
4181  const auto& subName = _SubList[0];
4182  const auto& shadowSub = _ShadowSubList[0];
4183  const auto& sub = shadowSub.oldName.empty() ? subName : shadowSub.oldName;
4184  if (exporting) {
4185  std::string exportName;
4186  writer.Stream() << "\" sub=\""
4187  << encodeAttribute(exportSubName(exportName, _pcLink, sub.c_str()));
4188  if (!shadowSub.oldName.empty() && shadowSub.newName == subName) {
4189  writer.Stream() << "\" " ATTR_MAPPED "=\"1";
4190  }
4191  }
4192  else {
4193  writer.Stream() << "\" sub=\"" << encodeAttribute(sub);
4194  if (!sub.empty()) {
4195  if (sub != subName) {
4196  writer.Stream() << "\" " ATTR_SHADOWED "=\"" << encodeAttribute(subName);
4197  }
4198  else if (!shadowSub.newName.empty()) {
4199  writer.Stream()
4200  << "\" " ATTR_SHADOW "=\"" << encodeAttribute(shadowSub.newName);
4201  }
4202  }
4203  }
4204  writer.Stream() << "\"/>" << std::endl;
4205  }
4206  else {
4207  writer.Stream() << "\" count=\"" << _SubList.size() << "\">" << std::endl;
4208  writer.incInd();
4209  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < _SubList.size(); i++) {
4210  const auto& shadow = _ShadowSubList[i];
4211  // shadow.oldName stores the old style element name. For backward
4212  // compatibility reason, we shall store the old name into attribute
4213  // 'value' whenever possible.
4214  const auto& sub = shadow.oldName.empty() ? _SubList[i] : shadow.oldName;
4215  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "<Sub value=\"";
4216  if (exporting) {
4217  std::string exportName;
4218  writer.Stream() << encodeAttribute(exportSubName(exportName, _pcLink, sub.c_str()));
4219  if (!shadow.oldName.empty() && shadow.newName == _SubList[i]) {
4220  writer.Stream() << "\" " ATTR_MAPPED "=\"1";
4221  }
4222  }
4223  else {
4224  writer.Stream() << encodeAttribute(sub);
4225  if (!_SubList[i].empty()) {
4226  if (sub != _SubList[i]) {
4227  writer.Stream()
4228  << "\" " ATTR_SHADOWED "=\"" << encodeAttribute(_SubList[i]);
4229  }
4230  else if (!shadow.newName.empty()) {
4231  writer.Stream()
4232  << "\" " ATTR_SHADOW "=\"" << encodeAttribute(shadow.newName);
4233  }
4234  }
4235  }
4236  writer.Stream() << "\"/>" << endl;
4237  }
4238  writer.decInd();
4239  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "</XLink>" << endl;
4240  }
4241 }

4243 void PropertyXLink::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
4244 {
4245  // read my element
4246  reader.readElement("XLink");
4247  std::string stampAttr, file;
4248  if (reader.hasAttribute("stamp")) {
4249  stampAttr = reader.getAttribute("stamp");
4250  }
4251  if (reader.hasAttribute("file")) {
4252  file = reader.getAttribute("file");
4253  }
4254 
4255  setFlag(LinkAllowPartial,
4256  reader.hasAttribute("partial") && reader.getAttributeAsInteger("partial"));
4257  std::string name;
4258  if (file.empty()) {
4259  name = reader.getName(reader.getAttribute("name"));
4260  }
4261  else {
4262  name = reader.getAttribute("name");
4263  }
4264 
4265  assert(getContainer()->isDerivedFrom<App::DocumentObject>());
4266  DocumentObject* object = nullptr;
4267  if (!name.empty() && file.empty()) {
4268  DocumentObject* parent = static_cast<DocumentObject*>(getContainer());
4269  Document* document = parent->getDocument();
4270  object = document ? document->getObject(name.c_str()) : nullptr;
4271  if (!object) {
4272  if (reader.isVerbose()) {
4273  FC_WARN("Lost link to '" << name
4274  << "' while loading, maybe "
4275  "an object was not loaded correctly");
4276  }
4277  }
4278  }
4279 
4280  std::vector<std::string> subs;
4281  std::vector<ShadowSub> shadows;
4282  std::vector<int> mapped;
4283  bool restoreLabel = false;
4284  if (reader.hasAttribute("sub")) {
4285  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_MAPPED)) {
4286  mapped.push_back(0);
4287  }
4288  subs.emplace_back();
4289  auto& subname = subs.back();
4290  shadows.emplace_back();
4291  auto& shadow = shadows.back();
4292  shadow.oldName = importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute("sub"), restoreLabel);
4293  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_SHADOWED) && !IGNORE_SHADOW) {
4294  subname = shadow.newName =
4295  importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute(ATTR_SHADOWED), restoreLabel);
4296  }
4297  else {
4298  subname = shadow.oldName;
4299  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_SHADOW) && !IGNORE_SHADOW) {
4300  shadow.newName =
4301  importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute(ATTR_SHADOW), restoreLabel);
4302  }
4303  }
4304  }
4305  else if (reader.hasAttribute("count")) {
4306  int count = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("count");
4307  subs.resize(count);
4308  shadows.resize(count);
4309  for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
4310  reader.readElement("Sub");
4311  shadows[i].oldName = importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute("value"), restoreLabel);
4312  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_SHADOWED) && !IGNORE_SHADOW) {
4313  subs[i] = shadows[i].newName =
4314  importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute(ATTR_SHADOWED), restoreLabel);
4315  }
4316  else {
4317  subs[i] = shadows[i].oldName;
4318  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_SHADOW) && !IGNORE_SHADOW) {
4319  shadows[i].newName =
4320  importSubName(reader, reader.getAttribute(ATTR_SHADOW), restoreLabel);
4321  }
4322  }
4323  if (reader.hasAttribute(ATTR_MAPPED)) {
4324  mapped.push_back(i);
4325  }
4326  }
4327  reader.readEndElement("XLink");
4328  }
4329  setFlag(LinkRestoreLabel, restoreLabel);
4330 
4331  if (name.empty()) {
4332  setValue(nullptr);
4333  return;
4334  }
4335 
4336  if (!file.empty() || (!object && !name.empty())) {
4337  this->stamp = stampAttr;
4338  setValue(std::move(file), std::move(name), std::move(subs), std::move(shadows));
4339  }
4340  else {
4341  setValue(object, std::move(subs), std::move(shadows));
4342  }
4343  _mapped = std::move(mapped);
4344 }

4583 void PropertyXLink::setPyObject(PyObject* value)
4584 {
4585  if (PySequence_Check(value)) {
4586  Py::Sequence seq(value);
4587  if (seq.size() != 2) {
4588  throw Base::ValueError("Expect input sequence of size 2");
4589  }
4590  std::vector<std::string> subs;
4591  Py::Object pyObj(seq[0].ptr());
4592  Py::Object pySub(seq[1].ptr());
4593  if (pyObj.isNone()) {
4594  setValue(nullptr);
4595  return;
4596  }
4597  else if (!PyObject_TypeCheck(pyObj.ptr(), &DocumentObjectPy::Type)) {
4598  throw Base::TypeError("Expect the first element to be of 'DocumentObject'");
4599  }
4600  PropertyString propString;
4601  if (pySub.isString()) {
4602  propString.setPyObject(pySub.ptr());
4603  subs.push_back(propString.getStrValue());
4604  }
4605  else if (pySub.isSequence()) {
4606  Py::Sequence seq(pySub);
4607  subs.reserve(seq.size());
4608  for (Py_ssize_t i = 0; i < seq.size(); ++i) {
4609  Py::Object sub(seq[i]);
4610  if (!sub.isString()) {
4611  throw Base::TypeError("Expect only string inside second argument");
4612  }
4613  propString.setPyObject(sub.ptr());
4614  subs.push_back(propString.getStrValue());
4615  }
4616  }
4617  else {
4618  throw Base::TypeError("Expect the second element to be a string or sequence of string");
4619  }
4620  setValue(static_cast<DocumentObjectPy*>(pyObj.ptr())->getDocumentObjectPtr(),
4621  std::move(subs));
4622  }
4623  else if (PyObject_TypeCheck(value, &(DocumentObjectPy::Type))) {
4624  setValue(static_cast<DocumentObjectPy*>(value)->getDocumentObjectPtr());
4625  }
4626  else if (Py_None == value) {
4627  setValue(nullptr);
4628  }
4629  else {
4630  throw Base::TypeError(
4631  "type must be 'DocumentObject', 'None', or '(DocumentObject, SubName)' or "
4632  "'DocumentObject, [SubName..])");
4633  }
4634 }

5072  }

5086  catch (Base::Exception&) {

5088  "Invalid type inside sequence. Must be type of (DocumentObject, (subname...))");
5089  }

5226 Property* PropertyXLinkSubList::CopyOnLinkReplace(const App::DocumentObject* parent,
5227  App::DocumentObject* oldObj,
5228  App::DocumentObject* newObj) const
5229 {
5230  std::unique_ptr<Property> copy;
5231  PropertyXLinkSub* copied = nullptr;
5232  std::set<std::string> subs;
5233  auto it = _Links.begin();
5234  for (; it != _Links.end(); ++it) {
5235  copy.reset(it->CopyOnLinkReplace(parent, oldObj, newObj));
5236  if (copy) {
5237  copied = static_cast<PropertyXLinkSub*>(copy.get());
5238  if (copied->getValue() == newObj) {
5239  for (auto& sub : copied->getSubValues()) {
5240  subs.insert(sub);
5241  }
5242  }
5243  break;
5244  }
5245  }
5246  if (!copy) {
5247  return nullptr;
5248  }
5249  std::unique_ptr<PropertyXLinkSubList> p(new PropertyXLinkSubList);
5250  for (auto iter = _Links.begin(); iter != it; ++iter) {
5251  if (iter->getValue() == newObj && copied->getValue() == newObj) {
5252  // merge subnames in case new object already exists
5253  for (auto& sub : iter->getSubValues()) {
5254  if (subs.insert(sub).second) {
5255  copied->_SubList.push_back(sub);
5256  }
5257  }
5258  }
5259  else {
5260  p->_Links.emplace_back();
5261  iter->copyTo(p->_Links.back());
5262  }
5263  }
5264  p->_Links.emplace_back();
5265  copied->copyTo(p->_Links.back());
5266  copied = &p->_Links.back();
5267  for (++it; it != _Links.end(); ++it) {
5268  if ((it->getValue() == newObj || it->getValue() == oldObj)
5269  && copied->getValue() == newObj) {
5270  // merge subnames in case new object already exists
5271  for (auto& sub : it->getSubValues()) {
5272  if (subs.insert(sub).second) {
5273  copied->_SubList.push_back(sub);
5274  }
5275  }
5276  continue;
5277  }
5278  p->_Links.emplace_back();
5279  copy.reset(it->CopyOnLinkReplace(parent, oldObj, newObj));
5280  if (copy) {
5281  static_cast<PropertyXLinkSub&>(*copy).copyTo(p->_Links.back());
5282  }
5283  else {
5284  it->copyTo(p->_Links.back());
5285  }
5286  }
5287  return p.release();
5288 }

5384  auto subnames = l.getSubValues(newStyle);
5385  if (subnames.empty()) {
5386  subnames.emplace_back("");
5387  }
5388  for (auto& sub : subnames) {
5389  objs.push_back(obj);
5390  subs->push_back(std::move(sub));
5391  }
5392  }
5393  }
5394  }

5397 // Same algorithm as _getLinksTo above, but returns all matches
5398 void PropertyXLinkSubList::_getLinksToList(
5399  std::vector<App::ObjectIdentifier>& identifiers,
5400  App::DocumentObject* obj,
5401  const char* subname,
5402  const std::vector<std::string>& subs,
5403  const std::vector<PropertyLinkBase::ShadowSub>& shadows) const
5404 {
5405  if (!subname) {
5406  identifiers.emplace_back(*this);
5407  return;
5408  }
5409  App::SubObjectT objT(obj, subname);
5410  auto subObject = objT.getSubObject();
5411  auto subElement = objT.getOldElementName();
5412 
5413  int i = -1;
5414  for (const auto& sub : subs) {
5415  ++i;
5416  if (sub == subname) {
5417  identifiers.emplace_back(*this, i);
5418  continue;
5419  }
5420  if (!subObject) {
5421  continue;
5422  }
5423  // There is a subobject and the subname doesn't match our current entry
5424  App::SubObjectT sobjT(obj, sub.c_str());
5425  if (sobjT.getSubObject() == subObject && sobjT.getOldElementName() == subElement) {
5426  identifiers.emplace_back(*this, i);
5427  continue;
5428  }
5429  // The oldElementName ( short, I.E. "Edge5" ) doesn't match.
5430  if (i < (int)shadows.size()) {
5431  const auto& [shadowNewName, shadowOldName] = shadows[i];
5432  if (shadowNewName == subname || shadowOldName == subname) {
5433  identifiers.emplace_back(*this, i);
5434  continue;
5435  }
5436  if (!subObject) {
5437  continue;
5438  }
5439  App::SubObjectT shadowobjT(obj,
5440  shadowNewName.empty() ? shadowOldName.c_str()
5441  : shadowNewName.c_str());
5442  if (shadowobjT.getSubObject() == subObject
5443  && shadowobjT.getOldElementName() == subElement) {
5444  identifiers.emplace_back(*this, i);
5445  continue;
5446  }
5447  }
5448  }
5449 }

5482 bool PropertyXLinkSubList::adjustLink(const std::set<App::DocumentObject*>& inList)
5483 {
5484  if (_pcScope == LinkScope::Hidden) {
5485  return false;
5486  }
5487  std::map<App::DocumentObject*, std::vector<std::string>> values;
5488  bool touched = false;
5489  int count = 0;
5490  for (auto& l : _Links) {
5491  auto obj = l.getValue();
5492  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
5493  ++count;
5494  continue;
5495  }
5496  if (inList.count(obj) && adjustLinkSubs(this, inList, obj, l._SubList, &values)) {
5497  touched = true;
5498  }
5499  }
5500  if (touched) {
5501  decltype(_Links) tmp;
5502  if (count) {
5503  // XLink allows detached state, i.e. with closed external document. So
5504  // we need to preserve empty link
5505  for (auto it = _Links.begin(), itNext = it; it != _Links.end(); it = itNext) {
5506  ++itNext;
5507  if (!it->getValue()) {
5508  tmp.splice(tmp.end(), _Links, it);
5509  }
5510  }
5511  }
5512  setValues(std::move(values));
5513  _Links.splice(_Links.end(), tmp);
5514  }
5515  return touched;
5516 }

5689 void PropertyXLinkContainer::breakLink(App::DocumentObject* obj, bool clear)
5690 {
5691  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
5692  return;
5693  }
5694  auto owner = dynamic_cast<App::DocumentObject*>(getContainer());
5695  if (!owner || !owner->isAttachedToDocument()) {
5696  return;
5697  }
5698  if (!clear || obj != owner) {
5699  auto it = _Deps.find(obj);
5700  if (it == _Deps.end()) {
5701  return;
5702  }
5703  aboutToSetValue();
5704  onBreakLink(obj);
5705  if (obj->getDocument() != owner->getDocument()) {
5706  _XLinks.erase(obj->getFullName());
5707  }
5708  else if (!it->second) {
5709  obj->_removeBackLink(owner);
5710  }
5711  _Deps.erase(it);
5712  onRemoveDep(obj);
5713  hasSetValue();
5714  return;
5715  }
5716  if (obj != owner) {
5717  return;
5718  }
5719  for (auto& v : _Deps) {
5720  auto key = v.first;
5721  if (!key || !key->isAttachedToDocument()) {
5722  continue;
5723  }
5724  onBreakLink(key);
5725  if (!v.second && key->getDocument() == owner->getDocument()) {
5726  key->_removeBackLink(owner);
5727  }
5728  }
5729  _XLinks.clear();
5730  _Deps.clear();
5731 }

5803 void PropertyXLinkContainer::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
5804 {
5805  reader.readElement("XLinks");
5806  auto count = reader.getAttributeAsUnsigned("count");
5807  _XLinkRestores = std::make_unique<std::vector<RestoreInfo>>(count);
5808 
5809  if (reader.hasAttribute("hidden")) {
5810  std::istringstream iss(reader.getAttribute("hidden"));
5811  int index;
5812  while (iss >> index) {
5813  if (index >= 0 && index < static_cast<int>(count)) {
5814  _XLinkRestores->at(index).hidden = true;
5815  }
5816  }
5817  }
5818 
5819  if (reader.hasAttribute("docs")) {
5820  auto docCount = reader.getAttributeAsUnsigned("docs");
5821  _DocMap.clear();
5822  for (unsigned i = 0; i < docCount; ++i) {
5823  reader.readElement("DocMap");
5824  auto index = reader.getAttributeAsUnsigned("index");
5825  if (index >= count) {
5826  FC_ERR(propertyName(this) << " invalid document map entry");
5827  continue;
5828  }
5829  auto& info = _XLinkRestores->at(index);
5830  info.docName = reader.getAttribute("name");
5831  info.docLabel = reader.getAttribute("label");
5832  }
5833  }
5834 
5835  for (auto& info : *_XLinkRestores) {
5836  info.xlink.reset(createXLink());
5837  if (info.hidden) {
5838  info.xlink->setScope(LinkScope::Hidden);
5839  }
5840  info.xlink->Restore(reader);
5841  }
5842  reader.readEndElement("XLinks");
5843 }
